<div class="container-analytics-dash">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col">
      <div class="career-summary">
        <div class="chart-title text-center">Your Total Score</div>
        <%= column_chart(@career_options_and_scores, id: "users-chart", colors: ["#e21d60", "#00bfbd"],label: "Cumulative Score", ytitle: "Weighted Score"
) %>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col text-center central-section-analytics">
      <div class="welcome">Welcome <span class="pink-bold welcome"><%= current_user.name.capitalize %></span></div>
      <div class="middle">
        Your top scored career option is
        <div class="top-option"><%= @top_career_option %></div>
        <br>
        Your responses show that you are a <span class="percentage"><%= @first_percentage %>%</span> fit for <%= @first_career_option.option %> and a <span class="percentage"><%= @second_percentage %>%</span> fit for <%= @second_career_option.option %>.
      </div>
      <div class="bottom">
        <div class="btn-ghost mb-2">
          Find resources
        </div>
        <div class="btn-ghost">
          Retake Assessment</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
      <div class="chart-title text-center">Your Priorities</div>
      <%= bar_chart(@priorities_plucked_with_names_ordered_by_score, id: "bar-chart", colors: ["#e21d60"], min: 0, max: 10, xtitle: "Score", options: {
  scales: {
    yAxes: [{
      display: false
    }],
    xAxes: [{
      scaleLabel: {
        display: true,
        labelString: 'Score'
      }
    }]
  }
}) %>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col">
        <div class="detail-bar-view">
          <div class="chart-title text-center">Detailed Comparison</div>
          <%= column_chart(@weighted_answers_with_job_title, id: "user-chart", colors: ["#e21d60", "#00bfbd"],label: "Cumulative Score", ytitle: "Weighted Score", legend: true) %>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col">
        <div class="chart-title text-center">Recommended for you</div>
        <div class="articles-analytics-container">
          <div class="article-card text-decoration-none">
            <%= link_to "https://hbr.org/2020/07/building-work-life-boundaries-in-the-wfh-era", class: "text-decoration-none height" do %>
              <div class="card-content-analytics" >
                <div class="card-header-analytics">Building Work-Life Boundaries in the WFH Era</div>
                <div class="card-body-analytics">How to help yourself — and your employees — find time and space to be productive. by Nancy P. Rothbard
                </div>
              </div>
            <% end %>
          </div>
          <div class="article-card text-decoration-none" >
            <%= link_to "https://hbr.org/2021/12/is-your-burnout-from-too-much-work-or-too-little-impact", class: "text-decoration-none height" do %>
              <div class="card-content-analytics">
                <div class="card-header-analytics">Is Your Burnout From Too Much Work or Too Little Impact?</div>
                <div class="card-body-analytics">When it comes to burnout, it’s natural to assume that by lessening our workload we can fight the culprit. On the contrary, research shows underutilisation might be the cause”
                </div>
              </div>
            <% end %>
          </div>
          <div class="article-card text-decoration-none">
            <%= link_to "https://hbr.org/2023/02/how-to-answer-what-are-your-salary-expectations
", class: "text-decoration-none height" do %>
              <div class="card-content-analytics" >
                <div class="card-header-analytics">How to Answer “What Are Your Salary Expectations?”
                </div>
                <div class="card-body-analytics">Many interview questions inspire dread in interviewees — one is especially complicated: “What are your salary expectations?”
                </div>
              </div>
            <% end %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
